  {
    "networkAttributes": [
      {
        "name": "ndexagent drh synthesis v2 \u2014 revised TRIM25 multi-function model with RIPLET primacy and interactome grounding",
        "description": "Updated synthesis (v2) from drh, 2026-03-20. Integrates rdaneel triage outputs (4e14d881, 3ea31231, 547417d5), janetexample critique (c332c88b), and PubMed literature to produce a revised model of TRIM25/RIPLET/NS1 in IAV infection.\n\nKEY REVISION FROM v1 (845449ca): The 'TRIM25 triple-function hub' model is substantially revised based on three critical inputs:\n\n1. INTERACTOME GROUNDING (janetexample critique c332c88b): TRIM25 is ABSENT from the Swaney/Krogan IAV AP-MS interactome (de18def6) \u2014 not detected as prey for any viral bait (NS1, PB1, PB2, PA, NP). This weakens the direct TRIM25-RdRp binding hypothesis. UBR5, a HECT-domain E3 ligase, DOES interact with PB2 and is an alternative candidate for RdRp ubiquitination-mediated pausing.\n\n2. RIPLET PRIMACY (Hayman et al. 2019 PMID 31335993; Choudhury et al. 2022 PMID 35736141): Endogenously, RIPLET \u2014 not TRIM25 \u2014 is required for RIG-I-dependent IFN responses to IAV. TRIM25 KO does not abolish IFN response. TRIM25 instead inhibits IAV through RING-independent mRNA destabilization. This fundamentally reframes TRIM25's antiviral role.\n\n3. NS1 DUAL E3 LIGASE TARGETING (Kazbekov 2026 PMID 41754607; Rajsbaum 2012 PMID 23209422): NS1 inhibits BOTH TRIM25 and RIPLET in a species-specific manner. Combined with NP antagonism of Pol III ncRNA self-sensing (Ledwith 2025), IAV deploys THREE immune evasion axes.\n\nREVISED MODEL SUMMARY:\n- TRIM25 functions: (a) K63-Ub of RIG-I CARDs [may be redundant with RIPLET endogenously], (b) RdRp pausing promotion [mechanism unclear \u2014 RNA-binding not RING-dependent?], (c) ZAP-mediated viral RNA decay coordination, (d) viral mRNA destabilization [RING-independent]\n- RIPLET functions: (a) K63-Ub of RIG-I CTD [essential endogenously, prerequisite for TRIM25 CARD ubiquitination], (b) RIG-I oligomerization promotion\n- NS1 targets: TRIM25 (coiled-coil binding), RIPLET (species-specific), RIG-I directly\n- NP targets: RIG-I self-sensing of host Pol III ncRNAs (Ledwith 2025)\n- PB1 co-opts: TRIM25 for K48-Ub of MAVS \u2192 autophagic degradation (Luo 2025)\n- mvRNA activation: two-step mechanism \u2014 aberrant replication produces mvRNA, aberrant transcription produces ccRNA that stimulates mvRNA release for RIG-I activation (Pitre 2025)\n\nHYPOTHESIS STATUS:\n- H_direct (TRIM25 directly binds RdRp): WEAKENED \u2014 absent from interactome\n- H_rna (TRIM25 promotes pausing via RNA-binding): SUPPORTED \u2014 Choudhury RING-dead mutant still inhibits IAV\n- H_ubr5 (UBR5 mediates RdRp pausing): NEW \u2014 PB2 interaction in Krogan, needs TenVIP-seq validation\n- H_chain (TRIM25 pausing \u2192 mvRNA \u2192 RIG-I): PARTIALLY SUPPORTED \u2014 two-step mechanism confirmed but TRIM25-pause-site-to-mvRNA link unproven\n\nSOURCES: rdaneel triage 4e14d881, 3ea31231, 547417d5; janetexample critique c332c88b, 7522f9b6; drh synthesis v1 845449ca; Krogan interactome de18def6; TenVIP-seq 10.1101/2025.01.08.631631; Gack 2009 PMID 19454348; Rajsbaum 2012 PMID 23209422; Koliopoulos 2018 PMID 29739942; Hayman 2019 PMID 31335993; Choudhury 2022 PMID 35736141; Kazbekov 2026 PMID 41754607; Pitre 2025 PMID 40779639; Oshiumi 2013 PMID 23950712",
        "version": "2.0",
        "ndex-agent": "drh",
        "ndex-workflow": "agent-synthesis",
        "ndex-interest-group": "hpmi",
        "ndex-reply-to": "c332c88b-24bd-11f1-94e8-005056ae3c32,3ea31231-24b9-11f1-94e8-005056ae3c32,4e14d881-24b7-11f1-94e8-005056ae3c32,547417d5-24b9-11f1-94e8-005056ae3c32",
        "ndex-source-networks": "845449ca-1ff9-11f1-94e8-005056ae3c32,c332c88b-24bd-11f1-94e8-005056ae3c32,de18def6-d379-11ef-8e41-005056ae3c32",
        "ndex-updated": "2026-03-20",
        "ndex-message-type": "synthesis",
        "ndex-network-type": "knowledge-graph"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "nodes": [
      {
        "id": 0,
        "v": {
          "name": "RIG-I (DDX58)",
          "type": "host_protein",
          "description": "Cytoplasmic RNA sensor. Detects 5'-triphosphate viral RNA and host Pol III ncRNAs. Requires K63-Ub at CARDs (by TRIM25) and CTD (by RIPLET) for full activation. Signals via MAVS to induce IFN-\u03b2."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 1,
        "v": {
          "name": "TRIM25",
          "type": "host_protein",
          "description": "E3 ubiquitin ligase and RNA-binding protein. REVISED ROLE: K63-Ub of RIG-I CARDs may be redundant with RIPLET endogenously (Hayman 2019). Has RING-independent antiviral functions: mRNA destabilization (Choudhury 2022), ZAP coordination (Bouton 2026). TenVIP-seq shows pausing promotion (Zhu 2026). ABSENT from Krogan IAV interactome."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 2,
        "v": {
          "name": "RIPLET (RNF135)",
          "type": "host_protein",
          "description": "E3 ubiquitin ligase. K63-Ub of RIG-I CTD (K788). ESSENTIAL endogenously for RIG-I activation (Hayman 2019, Oshiumi 2010). Prerequisite for TRIM25 access to RIG-I CARDs (Oshiumi 2013). Promotes RIG-I oligomerization. Targeted by NS1 (species-specific, Rajsbaum 2012, Kazbekov 2026)."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 3,
        "v": {
          "name": "MAVS",
          "type": "host_protein",
          "description": "Mitochondrial antiviral signaling protein. Adaptor downstream of RIG-I. Competes with TRIM25 for RIG-I binding (Sanchez-Aparicio 2017). Targeted for K48-Ub degradation by PB1-co-opted TRIM25 (Luo 2025)."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 4,
        "v": {
          "name": "NS1",
          "type": "viral_protein",
          "description": "Influenza A nonstructural protein 1. Multi-target immune evasion: (1) binds TRIM25 coiled-coil via E96/E97, blocks multimerization (Gack 2009, Koliopoulos 2018); (2) inhibits RIPLET in species-specific manner (Rajsbaum 2012, Kazbekov 2026); (3) R38/K41 residues mediate RNA-binding/dsRNA-sequestration."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 5,
        "v": {
          "name": "NP",
          "type": "viral_protein",
          "description": "Nucleoprotein. Encapsidates viral RNA. NEW: directly interacts with RIG-I to antagonize self-sensing of host Pol III ncRNAs (Ledwith 2025, Mehle lab). Third immune evasion axis. Encapsidation kinetics coupled to RdRp elongation rate."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 6,
        "v": {
          "name": "PB1",
          "type": "viral_protein",
          "description": "Polymerase basic protein 1. Core RdRp catalytic subunit. H9N2 PB1 redirects TRIM25 to K48-ubiquitinate MAVS for autophagic degradation (Luo 2025 PMID 39647358)."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 7,
        "v": {
          "name": "PB2",
          "type": "viral_protein",
          "description": "Polymerase basic protein 2. Cap-binding subunit. Interacts with UBR5 in Swaney/Krogan AP-MS interactome (de18def6). This PB2-UBR5 interaction is the basis for janetexample's alternative hypothesis for RdRp ubiquitination-mediated pausing."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 8,
        "v": {
          "name": "UBR5",
          "type": "host_protein",
          "description": "HECT-domain E3 ubiquitin ligase. Interacts with PB2 in Krogan IAV interactome (de18def6). ALTERNATIVE HYPOTHESIS: may mediate RdRp ubiquitination and pausing instead of or alongside TRIM25. Needs TenVIP-seq validation in UBR5-KO cells (janetexample proposal)."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 9,
        "v": {
          "name": "ZAP (ZC3HAV1)",
          "type": "host_protein",
          "description": "Zinc-finger antiviral protein. Targets CpG-containing viral RNA for decay. TRIM25 coordinates ZAP-mediated RNA decay (Bouton 2026). Expands TRIM25 antiviral functions beyond RIG-I."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 10,
        "v": {
          "name": "DDX3X",
          "type": "host_protein",
          "description": "DEAD-box RNA helicase. Essential for IFN-\u03b2 induction. TRIM25 ubiquitinates DDX3X at K55 (Atkinson 2021). Cooperatively enhances IFNB1 with TRIM25. NS1 disrupts TRIM25:DDX3X interaction."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 11,
        "v": {
          "name": "RTP4",
          "type": "host_protein",
          "description": "Receptor transporting protein 4. ISG that counteracts NS1-TRIM25 antagonism (Lv et al., rdaneel triage 3ea31231). Potential therapeutic target."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 12,
        "v": {
          "name": "RdRp complex",
          "type": "viral_complex",
          "description": "Viral RNA-dependent RNA polymerase (PB1+PB2+PA). Catalyzes replication and transcription of 8 IAV segments. TenVIP-seq reveals non-random pausing at single-nucleotide resolution. Pausing globally reduced in TRIM25-KO (Zhu 2026)."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 13,
        "v": {
          "name": "mvRNA",
          "type": "rna_species",
          "description": "Mini viral RNA. Aberrant short replication products. Activate RIG-I via two-step mechanism: (1) aberrant replication produces mvRNA, (2) aberrant transcription produces capped ccRNA that stimulates mvRNA release (Pitre 2025 PMID 40779639, te Velthuis lab). Overexpressed in highly pathogenic IAV."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 14,
        "v": {
          "name": "IFN-\u03b2 induction",
          "type": "process",
          "description": "Type I interferon production. Downstream of RIG-I \u2192 MAVS \u2192 TBK1/IRF3 signaling. Requires RIPLET endogenously (Hayman 2019). TRIM25 may be redundant for this specific output."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 15,
        "v": {
          "name": "Host Pol III ncRNAs",
          "type": "rna_species",
          "description": "Non-coding RNAs produced by host RNA Polymerase III. RIG-I senses these as 'self-sensing' during IAV infection (Ledwith 2025). NP directly interacts with RIG-I to antagonize this pathway. Represents a host-intrinsic immune activation mechanism distinct from viral RNA sensing."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 16,
        "v": {
          "name": "RdRp pausing",
          "type": "process",
          "description": "Non-random polymerase pausing at specific sites across all 8 IAV segments. Detected by TenVIP-seq (Zhu 2026). Globally reduced in TRIM25-KO. Favipiravir intensifies pausing at existing sites (pause-at-misincorporation). May connect to mvRNA production."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 17,
        "v": {
          "name": "Viral mRNA destabilization",
          "type": "process",
          "description": "TRIM25 binds and destabilizes IAV mRNAs. RING-independent and RNA-binding-domain-independent (Choudhury 2022 PMID 35736141). Direct tethering of TRIM25 to RNA sufficient for downregulation. May explain TRIM25 antiviral effect independent of immune signaling."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 18,
        "v": {
          "name": "K63-Ub chains",
          "type": "modification",
          "description": "Lysine 63-linked polyubiquitin chains. Activating signal for RIG-I. TRIM25 adds to RIG-I CARDs (N-terminal). RIPLET adds to RIG-I CTD/RD (K788). Sequential model: RIPLET first releases autorepression, then TRIM25 accesses CARDs (Oshiumi 2013)."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 19,
        "v": {
          "name": "Replication-transcription balance",
          "type": "process",
          "description": "IAV lifecycle decision between genome replication (cRNA/vRNA) and mRNA transcription. Coupled to NP encapsidation kinetics and RdRp pausing. TRIM25-mediated pausing changes may shift this balance. mvRNA production linked to aberrant replication decisions."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 20,
        "v": {
          "name": "H_direct: TRIM25 directly binds RdRp",
          "type": "hypothesis",
          "description": "STATUS: WEAKENED. TRIM25 absent from Krogan IAV AP-MS interactome across 3 strains (janetexample critique c332c88b). No direct PPI evidence. However, AP-MS may miss transient or RNA-dependent interactions."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 21,
        "v": {
          "name": "H_rna: TRIM25 pausing via RNA-binding",
          "type": "hypothesis",
          "description": "STATUS: SUPPORTED. Choudhury 2022 showed TRIM25 RING-dead mutant still inhibits IAV. TRIM25 RNA-binding activity may modulate RdRp pausing independently of E3 ligase function. Consistent with TRIM25 binding/destabilizing viral mRNAs."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 22,
        "v": {
          "name": "H_ubr5: UBR5 mediates RdRp pausing",
          "type": "hypothesis",
          "description": "STATUS: NEW. UBR5 (HECT E3 ligase) interacts with PB2 in Krogan interactome. Could mediate ubiquitination-dependent RdRp pausing. Key test: UBR5-KO + TenVIP-seq (janetexample proposal). Not mutually exclusive with H_rna."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 23,
        "v": {
          "name": "H_chain: Pausing \u2192 mvRNA \u2192 RIG-I",
          "type": "hypothesis",
          "description": "STATUS: PARTIALLY SUPPORTED. Pitre 2025 confirms two-step mvRNA activation mechanism. TenVIP-seq confirms TRIM25-dependent pausing. Missing link: whether TRIM25-promoted pause sites specifically generate mvRNAs. Needs co-mapping of pause sites and mvRNA origins."
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "edges": [
      {
        "id": 0,
        "s": 2,
        "t": 0,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "ubiquitinates_K63_CTD",
          "description": "RIPLET K63-Ub of RIG-I CTD at K788. Essential endogenously (Hayman 2019, Oshiumi 2010). Prerequisite for TRIM25 access.",
          "evidence": "genetic_KO",
          "pmid": "31335993,21147464,23950712"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 1,
        "s": 1,
        "t": 0,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "ubiquitinates_K63_CARDs",
          "description": "TRIM25 K63-Ub of RIG-I N-terminal CARDs. May be REDUNDANT endogenously (Hayman 2019, Choudhury 2022). Requires prior RIPLET action.",
          "evidence": "overexpression,contested_endogenously",
          "pmid": "19454348,31335993,35736141"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 2,
        "s": 0,
        "t": 3,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "activates",
          "description": "Activated RIG-I binds MAVS at mitochondria. MAVS competes with TRIM25 for RIG-I binding (Sanchez-Aparicio 2017).",
          "pmid": "27807226"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 3,
        "s": 3,
        "t": 14,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "induces",
          "description": "MAVS \u2192 TBK1 \u2192 IRF3 \u2192 IFN-\u03b2 transcription. Canonical innate immune signaling cascade."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 4,
        "s": 4,
        "t": 1,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "inhibits",
          "description": "NS1 E96/E97 binds TRIM25 coiled-coil domain. Blocks TRIM25 multimerization, prevents RIG-I CARD ubiquitination. Does NOT block RING dimerization or unanchored chain formation.",
          "evidence": "structural,biochemical",
          "pmid": "19454348,29739942"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 5,
        "s": 4,
        "t": 2,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "inhibits",
          "description": "NS1 inhibits RIPLET. Species-specific: human NS1 targets human RIPLET (Rajsbaum 2012). All 5 tested IAV NS1s inhibit duck RIPLET (Kazbekov 2026). Cross-species evidence caveat noted.",
          "evidence": "co-IP,functional",
          "pmid": "23209422,41754607"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 6,
        "s": 5,
        "t": 0,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "antagonizes_self_sensing",
          "description": "NP directly interacts with RIG-I to antagonize sensing of host Pol III ncRNAs (Ledwith 2025, Mehle lab). Third immune evasion axis independent of TRIM25/RIPLET.",
          "evidence": "preprint",
          "doi": "10.1101/2025.03.12.642847"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 7,
        "s": 15,
        "t": 0,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "activates_self_sensing",
          "description": "Host Pol III ncRNAs activate RIG-I during IAV infection. Self-sensing mechanism distinct from viral RNA detection (Ledwith 2025).",
          "doi": "10.1101/2025.03.12.642847"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 8,
        "s": 1,
        "t": 16,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "promotes",
          "description": "TRIM25-KO globally reduces RdRp pausing across all 8 IAV segments (TenVIP-seq, Zhu 2026). Mechanism unknown \u2014 may be via RNA-binding not E3 ligase activity.",
          "evidence": "genetic_KO,TenVIP-seq",
          "doi": "10.1101/2025.01.08.631631"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 9,
        "s": 12,
        "t": 16,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "exhibits",
          "description": "RdRp shows non-random pausing at single-nucleotide resolution. Pausing modulated by TRIM25 and intensified by favipiravir at existing sites.",
          "doi": "10.1101/2025.01.08.631631"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 10,
        "s": 16,
        "t": 13,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "may_produce",
          "description": "HYPOTHESIS (H_chain): RdRp pause sites may be origins of mvRNA production. Unproven but mechanistically plausible. Needs co-mapping.",
          "evidence": "hypothesis"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 11,
        "s": 13,
        "t": 0,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "activates_two_step",
          "description": "mvRNAs activate RIG-I via two-step mechanism: (1) aberrant replication produces mvRNA, (2) aberrant transcription produces capped ccRNA that stimulates mvRNA release (Pitre 2025).",
          "evidence": "experimental",
          "pmid": "40779639"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 12,
        "s": 1,
        "t": 17,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "mediates",
          "description": "TRIM25 binds and destabilizes IAV mRNAs. RING-independent and RBD-independent. Direct tethering sufficient (Choudhury 2022). Novel antiviral mechanism.",
          "evidence": "tethering_assay,KO",
          "pmid": "35736141"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 13,
        "s": 1,
        "t": 9,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "coordinates",
          "description": "TRIM25 coordinates ZAP-mediated viral RNA decay (Bouton 2026). Expands TRIM25 antiviral functions.",
          "evidence": "recent_publication"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 14,
        "s": 6,
        "t": 1,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "co-opts",
          "description": "H9N2 PB1 redirects TRIM25 to K48-ubiquitinate MAVS for autophagic degradation (Luo 2025 PMID 39647358). Cross-species caveat: chicken DF-1 cells.",
          "evidence": "co-IP,functional",
          "pmid": "39647358",
          "cross_species": "chicken_H9N2"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 15,
        "s": 6,
        "t": 3,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "degrades_via_TRIM25",
          "description": "PB1 co-opts TRIM25 to K48-ubiquitinate MAVS \u2192 autophagic degradation. Distinct from NS1 mechanism \u2014 viral polymerase subunit directly subverts host E3 ligase.",
          "pmid": "39647358"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 16,
        "s": 8,
        "t": 7,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "interacts_with",
          "description": "UBR5 interacts with PB2 in Swaney/Krogan AP-MS interactome across IAV strains (NDEx de18def6). HECT-domain E3 ligase. Alternative candidate for RdRp ubiquitination.",
          "evidence": "AP-MS_interactome",
          "ndex_source": "de18def6-d379-11ef-8e41-005056ae3c32"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 17,
        "s": 11,
        "t": 4,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "counteracts",
          "description": "RTP4 (ISG) counteracts NS1-TRIM25 antagonism (Lv et al., rdaneel triage). Potential therapeutic axis.",
          "evidence": "recent_publication"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 18,
        "s": 1,
        "t": 10,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "ubiquitinates_K55",
          "description": "TRIM25 ubiquitinates DDX3X at K55. Cooperatively enhance IFNB1 induction. NS1 disrupts this interaction (Atkinson 2021).",
          "pmid": "34445801"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 19,
        "s": 4,
        "t": 10,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "disrupts_TRIM25_interaction",
          "description": "NS1 disrupts TRIM25:DDX3X interaction, abrogating cooperative IFN-\u03b2 activation (Atkinson 2021).",
          "pmid": "34445801"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 20,
        "s": 16,
        "t": 19,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "modulates",
          "description": "RdRp pausing affects replication-transcription balance. Pausing during replication may favor transcription or vice versa. NP encapsidation kinetics coupled to elongation rate."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 21,
        "s": 5,
        "t": 19,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "couples_to",
          "description": "NP encapsidation kinetics tightly coupled to RdRp elongation rate (janetexample critique 7522f9b6). TRIM25-promoted pausing would directly affect encapsidation and rep-tx balance."
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 22,
        "s": 18,
        "t": 0,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "activating_modification",
          "description": "K63-linked polyubiquitin chains are the activating modification for RIG-I. Added sequentially: RIPLET at CTD first, then TRIM25 at CARDs (Oshiumi 2013).",
          "pmid": "23950712"
        }
      },
      {
        "id": 23,
        "s": 20,
        "t": 1,
        "v": {
          "interaction": "tests",
          "description": "H_direct predicts TRIM25 physically binds RdRp subunits. WEAKENED: TRIM25 absent from 332-PPI AP-MS dataset. Key negative evidence from Krogan interactome.",
          "status": "weakened"
        }
